{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632717","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632717"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:43:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:43:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17436"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17436","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17436"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10126"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70902"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10126","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10126"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17436"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56369"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5425"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23726"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23829"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70902"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 78-year-old woman who lives with her adult son present to her GP for a routine check-up. During the consult, she appears anxious when discussing her living situation. Her GP suspects elder abuse.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common form of elder abuse?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Physical abuse","Psychological abuse","Financial exploitation","Sexual abuse","Neglect"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFinancial exploitation\u003C/strong\u003E involves the misuse or withholding of an older person\u0027s resources by another person. This can include theft, fraud, or coercion in financial matters.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other forms of abuse include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhysical abuse\u003C/strong\u003E involves causing physical pain or injury through actions such as hitting, pushing, or inappropriate restraint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESexual abuse\u003C/strong\u003E includes any non-consensual sexual contact with an elderly person.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsychological abuse\u003C/strong\u003E involves verbal or non-verbal acts causing fear, distress, or emotional pain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeglect\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the failure to provide for basic needs including food, shelter, healthcare, or protection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElder abuse often goes unreported due to shame, dependence on the perpetrator, or cognitive impairment. Different forms of abuse may occur simultaneously and can significantly impact an older person\u0027s quality of life and access to resources.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Elder abuse includes physical, psychological, financial, and sexual abuse, as well as neglect.","Financial exploitation is the most common form of elder abuse, occurring in up to 5% of older adults.","Healthcare providers have a legal obligation to report suspected cases of elder abuse."],"references":["Patel K, Bunachita S, Chiu H, Suresh P, Patel UK. Elder Abuse: A Comprehensive Overview and Physician-Associated Challenges. Cureus. 2021 Apr 8;13(4):e14375. doi: 10.7759/cureus.14375. PMID: 33987046; PMCID: PMC8110289."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56369"}},"que